        {
            "id":"good-company",
            "title":"Good Company",
            "services":["Brand Identity Design","Interior Design"],
            "date":"2025",
            "text": "Good Company has spent over a decade bringing ideas to fruition through fabrication. Their work spans scenic structures for weddings at the Plaza Hotel, set build-outs for brand activations in House of Blues, and most recently, a custom metal helix installation for the St. Louis Art Museum.</p><p>When they approached me, they were operating under an outdated visual identity and an unfinished studio space. While they had built a reputation for expert draping and seamless installs, Fabian, the owner, wanted the brand to better reflect the creativity and innovation behind their work.</p><p>The result was a brand and studio refresh that positioned Good Company for the artists, institutions and concept-driven clients it hopes to attract in the future.",
            "main":"/Portfolio-Content/instagram/main.webp",
            "media": [
